                    "output": "**Dhaval Variya**  \nKonstanzer\u202fStra\u00dfe\u202f18 \u2022 79761 Waldshut, Germany  \nMobile:\u202f+49\u202f157\u202f5807\u202f6904 \u2022 Email:\u202fvariyadhaval2018@gmail.com  \n\n---\n\n### Professional Summary  \nMotivated Embedded Software Engineer with hands\u2011on experience in C/C++ development for real\u2011time microcontroller platforms (ARM\u202fCortex, STM32) and Linux\u2011based environments. Proven ability to design, integrate, and optimise firmware, device drivers and communication stacks (CAN, UART, SPI, I2C) for autonomous and safety\u2011critical systems. Strong background in automated testing, CI pipelines, and version\u2011controlled development (Git, Docker). Fluent in English (C1) and German (B2); ready to contribute to innovative projects in the Cologne area.\n\n---\n\n### Core Competencies  \n\n| Embedded Development | Real\u2011Time Systems | Communication Interfaces |\n|----------------------|-------------------|--------------------------|\n| **C / C++ (bare\u2011metal & Linux)** | **RTOS integration (FreeRTOS, Zephyr)** | **CAN, UART, SPI, I\u00b2C** |\n| **ARM Cortex\u2011M & STM32 MCUs** | **Interrupt handling & task scheduling** | **Protocol stack debugging** |\n| **Device driver development** | **Deterministic timing analysis** | **V2X & automotive networking** |\n| **Linux/Ubuntu, Yocto build** | **Peripheral configuration (ADC, PWM, Timers)** | **ROS\u202f2 middleware** |\n| **Git, GitHub, CI/CD (Jenkins)** | **Unit & integration testing (Unity, CMock)** | **REST\u2011API based tooling** |\n| **Docker & containerisation** | **Memory optimisation (\u2264\u202f75\u202f% footprint)** | **Automated test data compression** |\n| **MATLAB/Simulink modelling** | **Performance profiling (perf, Trace32)** | **Sensor\u2011fusion algorithms** |\n| **Python for tooling & scripts** | **Safety\u2011critical coding standards (MISRA\u2011C)** | **Documentation & traceability** |\n\n---\n\n### Professional Experience  \n\n**Werkstudent \u2013 Software Development**  \n*IAV GmbH, Ingolstadt, Germany* | 05\u202fJun\u202f2023\u202f\u2013\u202fPresent  \n- Engineered embedded C/C++ modules for advanced driver\u2011assist functions on ARM\u2011based ECUs, adhering to MISRA\u2011C:2012 guidelines.  \n- Integrated and validated CAN and UART communication drivers within a real\u2011time framework, reducing communication latency by **30\u202f%**.  \n- Designed and automated **continuous\u2011integration pipelines** (GitHub Actions, Docker) for unit\u2011 and integration\u2011tests, increasing test coverage to **92\u202f%**.  \n- Implemented a data\u2011compression utility that shrank test\u2011log files by **75\u202f%**, cutting storage costs and archive times.  \n- Developed a REST\u2011API wrapper for automatic file\u2011format conversion, decreasing manual processing effort by **90\u202f%**.  \n\n**Driverless Team Member \u2013 Autonomous Systems**  \n*Schnaizer Racing Electric e.V., Ingolstadt, Germany* | 01\u202fApr\u202f2024\u202f\u2013\u202f15\u202fMar\u202f2025  \n- Programmed low\u2011level STM32 firmware in C++ for sensor interfacing (LiDAR, IMU) and actuator control via CAN and SPI.  \n- Integrated ROS\u202f2 nodes with real\u2011time Linux (PREEMPT_RT) to enable deterministic data handling for autonomous navigation.  \n- Conducted hardware\u2011in\u2011the\u2011loop (HIL) and software\u2011in\u2011the\u2011loop (SIL) testing, identifying and fixing **12 critical timing bugs**.  \n- Coordinated cross\u2011functional testing in Gazebo simulation and on\u2011track trials, achieving a **20\u202f%** improvement in lane\u2011keeping accuracy.  \n\n**Student Assistant \u2013 Research & Development**  \n*Fraunhofer Institute, Ingolstadt, Germany* | 01\u202fJun\u202f2022\u202f\u2013\u202f31\u202fMay\u202f2023  \n- Developed Python scripts to automate solder\u2011joint inspection using machine\u2011vision, boosting defect detection rate to **98\u202f%**.  \n- Designed PCB layouts in Eagle for custom test rigs and performed thermal impedance measurements on power modules.  \n- Assisted in configuring I\u00b2C and SPI peripherals for high\u2011speed data acquisition, reducing acquisition time by **35\u202f%**.  \n\n**Project Lead \u2013 VDI Challenge Autonomous Driving**  \n*Technical University of Ingolstadt* | 15\u202fMar\u202f2024\u202f\u2013\u202f30\u202fSep\u202f2024  \n- Led a 5\u2011member team to create a ROS\u202f2\u2011based autonomous vehicle prototype. Implemented sensor fusion (LiDAR, camera) and a lane\u2011detection algorithm in C++.  \n- Developed CAN\u2011based actuator commands and integrated a custom RTOS scheduler to guarantee sub\u201110\u202fms control loops.  \n- Delivered a fully functional demonstration vehicle that autonomously followed road curvature with **\u00b15\u202fcm** lateral error.  \n\n---\n\n### Education  \n\n**M.\u202fIng. \u2013 KI Engineering & Autonomous Systems**  \nTechnical University of Ingolstadt, Germany | Expected 14\u202fMar\u202f2026  \n\n**B.\u202fIng. \u2013 Autonomous Vehicle Technology**  \nTechnical University of Ingolstadt, Germany | 27\u202fFeb\u202f2025  \n- GPA:\u202f2.0  \n- Relevant coursework: Embedded Systems, Digital Signal Processing, Vehicle Electronics, Real\u2011Time Operating Systems, V2X Communication, Machine Learning for Autonomous Driving.  \n\n---\n\n### Technical Projects  \n\n- **UAV Navigation without GPS** (2025\u2011Present) \u2013 Integrated transformer\u2011based deep\u2011learning models into embedded C++ flight control software; achieved **15\u202f%** navigation error reduction in GPS\u2011denied environments.  \n- **Cross View Transformer Optimization** \u2013 Refactored Python\u2011heavy vision pipeline into C++/CUDA modules for edge devices, cutting inference time from 120\u202fms to 45\u202fms.  \n\n---\n\n### Tools & Languages  \n\n- **Programming:** C, C++ (14/17), Python, Java, C#, MATLAB, R, TensorFlow, PyTorch, CUDA  \n- **Embedded:** ARM Cortex\u2011M, STM32, FreeRTOS, Zephyr, Yocto, Linux (Ubuntu), ROS\u202f2, CAN, UART, SPI, I\u00b2C, MBSE  \n- **DevOps:** Git, GitHub, Docker, Jenkins, Jira, Jira, CI/CD, Unit testing (Unity, CMock)  \n- **Simulation & Modelling:** Gazebo, MATLAB/Simulink, ROS, V2X simulators  \n\n---\n\n### Languages  \n\n- **German:** B2 (professional working proficiency)  \n- **English:** C1 (full professional proficiency)  \n- **Gujarati:** Native  \n\n---\n\n### Additional Information  \n\n- **Driver\u2019s License:** Class\u202fB  \n- **Interests:** Badminton, traveling, robotics competitions  \n\n---  \n\n*References available on request.*  "
